Hello everyone!

Greetings from *Centre *for Innovation and *iBot Club!*

iBot*,* CFI's Robotics club, presents to you the first session-cum-workshop
of this semester:
*Introduction to Robotics: Mechanisms and Control*

Ever wanted to build cool robots armed with destructive mechanisms? If yes,
iBot is the place to be! The theme for this year's workshop is *Robowars*!
In this workshop*, *You will be building your own robots of destruction and
can pit against your friends for a showdown till death.

Please form groups of 5-8 and register in this form
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdf3WrZ6dV1PDyHZA-06CuC2JudaV4ttKbKJyX-uQgFlc8rGw/viewform>
for
the workshop. *It is compulsory to register for the workshop online*. The
registrants will later be contacted to inform about the time and date of
workshop. Also, each team needs to pay a *security fee* of 2500 INR for the
kits to be used in the workshop. This amount will be returned to you after
the semester, if you return the kits to us.

The session is open to students of all branches and years! Prerequisites:
None! Just enthu!

Deadline: *11:59 PM, Sunday 11th September*

P.S. Register soon for the workshop as we have limited number of kits!

Cheers!

